{"timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.912+0000", "rule_id": "19008", "severity": "INFO", "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure root is the only UID 0 account.", "source_ip": "Unknown", "agent": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "full_alert": {"agent": {"name": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "id": "001"}, "manager": {"name": "wazuh.manager"}, "data": {"sca": {"scan_id": "319070859", "check": {"result": "passed", "remediation": "Remove any users other than root with UID 0 or assign them a new UID if appropriate.", "file": ["/etc/passwd"], "compliance": {"mitre_tactics": "TA0001", "mitre_techniques": "T1548", "cis": "6.2.9", "mitre_mitigations": "M1026"}, "description": "Any account with UID 0 has superuser privileges on the system.", "id": "31183", "title": "Ensure root is the only UID 0 account.", "rationale": "This access must be limited to only the default root account and only from the system console. Administrative access must be through an unprivileged account using an approved mechanism as noted in Item 5.6 Ensure access to the su command is restricted."}, "type": "check", "policy": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0."}}, "rule": {"mail": false, "level": 3, "pci_dss": ["2.2"], "tsc": ["CC7.1", "CC7.2"], "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure root is the only UID 0 account.", "groups": ["sca"], "mitre_tactics": ["TA0001"], "mitre_techniques": ["T1548"], "cis": ["6.2.9"], "nist_800_53": ["CM.1"], "mitre_mitigations": ["M1026"], "gdpr": ["IV_35.7.d"], "firedtimes": 101, "id": "19008"}, "decoder": {"name": "sca"}, "input": {"type": "log"}, "@timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.912Z", "location": "sca", "id": "1776413938.1402595", "timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.912+0000"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.902+0000", "rule_id": "19008", "severity": "INFO", "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure password fields are not empty.", "source_ip": "Unknown", "agent": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "full_alert": {"agent": {"name": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "id": "001"}, "manager": {"name": "wazuh.manager"}, "data": {"sca": {"scan_id": "319070859", "check": {"result": "passed", "remediation": "If any accounts in the /etc/shadow file do not have a password, run the following command to lock the account until it can be determined why it does not have a password: # passwd -l <username> Also, check to see if the account is logged in and investigate what it is being used for to determine if it needs to be forced off.", "file": ["/etc/shadow"], "compliance": {"pci_dss_v4": {"0": "2.2.2,8.3.5,8.3.6,8.6.3"}, "cis_csc_v8": "5.2", "soc_2": "CC6.1", "nist_sp_800-53": "IA-5(1)", "mitre_tactics": "TA0003", "mitre_techniques": "T1078,T1078.001,T1078.003", "cis": "6.2.2", "cmmc_v2": {"0": "IA.L2-3.5.7"}, "iso_27001-2013": "A.9.4.3", "cis_csc_v7": "4.4", "mitre_mitigations": "M1027"}, "description": "An account with an empty password field means that anybody may log in as that user without providing a password.", "id": "31182", "title": "Ensure password fields are not empty.", "rationale": "All accounts must have passwords or be locked to prevent the account from being used by an unauthorized user."}, "type": "check", "policy": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0."}}, "rule": {"cis_csc_v8": ["5.2"], "mail": false, "level": 3, "pci_dss": ["2.2"], "tsc": ["CC7.1", "CC7.2"], "nist_sp_800-53": ["IA-5(1)"], "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure password fields are not empty.", "groups": ["sca"], "mitre_tactics": ["TA0003"], "mitre_techniques": ["T1078", "T1078.001", "T1078.003"], "cis": ["6.2.2"], "iso_27001-2013": ["A.9.4.3"], "nist_800_53": ["CM.1"], "mitre_mitigations": ["M1027"], "gdpr": ["IV_35.7.d"], "firedtimes": 100, "soc_2": ["CC6.1"], "id": "19008", "cis_csc_v7": ["4.4"]}, "decoder": {"name": "sca"}, "input": {"type": "log"}, "@timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.902Z", "location": "sca", "id": "1776413938.1399778", "timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.902+0000"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.892+0000", "rule_id": "19007", "severity": "MEDIUM", "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure accounts in /etc/passwd use shadowed passwords.", "source_ip": "Unknown", "agent": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "full_alert": {"agent": {"name": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "id": "001"}, "manager": {"name": "wazuh.manager"}, "data": {"sca": {"scan_id": "319070859", "check": {"result": "failed", "remediation": "Run the following command to set accounts to use shadowed passwords: # sed -e 's/^\\([a-zA-Z0-9_]*\\):[^:]*:/\\1:x:/' -i /etc/passwd Investigate to determine if the account is logged in and what it is being used for, to determine if it needs to be forced off.", "file": ["/etc/passwd"], "compliance": {"cis_csc_v8": "3.11", "hipaa": "164.312(a)(2)(iv),164.312(e)(2)(ii)", "nist_sp_800-53": "SC-28,SC-28(1)", "mitre_tactics": "TA0003", "mitre_techniques": "T1003,T1003.008", "cis": "6.2.1", "cmmc_v2": {"0": "AC.L2-3.1.19,IA.L2-3.5.10,MP.L2-3.8.1,SC.L2-3.13.11,SC.L2-3.13.16"}, "iso_27001-2013": "A.10.1.1", "mitre_mitigations": "M1027", "pci_dss_v4": {"0": "3.1.1,3.3.2,3.3.3,3.5.1,3.5.1.2,3.5.1.3,8.3.2"}, "soc_2": "CC6.1", "pci_dss_v3": {"2": {"1": "3.4,3.4.1,8.2.1"}}, "cis_csc_v7": "16.4"}, "description": "Local accounts can use shadowed passwords. With shadowed passwords, the passwords are saved in shadow password file, /etc/shadow, encrypted by a salted one-way hash. Accounts with a shadowed password have an x in the second field in /etc/passwd.", "id": "31181", "title": "Ensure accounts in /etc/passwd use shadowed passwords.", "rationale": "The /etc/passwd file also contains information like user ID's and group ID's that are used by many system programs. Therefore, the /etc/passwd file must remain world readable. In spite of encoding the password with a randomly-generated one-way hash function, an attacker could still break the system if they got access to the /etc/passwd file. This can be mitigated by using shadowed passwords, thus moving the passwords in the /etc/passwd file to /etc/shadow. The /etc/shadow file is set so only root will be able to read and write. This helps mitigate the risk of an attacker gaining access to the encoded passwords with which to perform a dictionary attack. Note: - All accounts must have passwords or be locked to prevent the account from being used by an unauthorized user. - A user account with an empty second field in /etc/passwd allows the account to be logged into by providing only the username."}, "type": "check", "policy": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0."}}, "rule": {"cis_csc_v8": ["3.11"], "mail": false, "level": 7, "pci_dss": ["2.2"], "tsc": ["CC7.1", "CC7.2"], "hipaa": ["164.312(a)(2)(iv)", "164.312(e)(2)(ii)"], "nist_sp_800-53": ["SC-28", "SC-28(1)"], "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure accounts in /etc/passwd use shadowed passwords.", "groups": ["sca"], "mitre_tactics": ["TA0003"], "mitre_techniques": ["T1003", "T1003.008"], "cis": ["6.2.1"], "iso_27001-2013": ["A.10.1.1"], "nist_800_53": ["CM.1"], "mitre_mitigations": ["M1027"], "gdpr": ["IV_35.7.d"], "firedtimes": 90, "soc_2": ["CC6.1"], "id": "19007", "cis_csc_v7": ["16.4"]}, "decoder": {"name": "sca"}, "input": {"type": "log"}, "@timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.892Z", "location": "sca", "id": "1776413938.1394832", "timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.892+0000"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.882+0000", "rule_id": "19009", "severity": "INFO", "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure sticky bit is set on all world-writable directories.", "source_ip": "Unknown", "agent": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "full_alert": {"agent": {"name": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "id": "001"}, "manager": {"name": "wazuh.manager"}, "data": {"sca": {"scan_id": "319070859", "check": {"result": "not applicable", "remediation": "Run the following command to set the sticky bit on all world writable directories: # df --local -P | awk '{if (NR!=1) print $6}' | xargs -I '{}' find '{}' -xdev -type d \\( -perm -0002 -a ! -perm -1000 \\) 2>/dev/null | xargs -I '{}' chmod a+t '{}'.", "reason": "Invalid path or wrong permissions to run command 'sh -c \"df --local -P 2> /dev/null | awk '{if (NR!=1) print $6}' | xargs -I '{}' find '{}' -xdev -type d \\\\( -perm -0002 -a ! -perm -1000 \\\\) 2>/dev/null\"'", "compliance": {"cis_csc_v8": "3.3,4.1", "hipaa": "164.308(a)(3)(i),164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A),164.312(a)(1)", "nist_sp_800-53": "AC-5,AC-6,CM-7(1),CM-9,SA-10", "mitre_tactics": "TA0004", "mitre_techniques": "T1548", "cis": "6.1.13", "cmmc_v2": {"0": "AC.L1-3.1.1,AC.L1-3.1.2,AC.L2-3.1.3,AC.L2-3.1.5,CM.L2-3.4.1,CM.L2-3.4.2,CM.L2-3.4.6,CM.L2-3.4.7,MP.L2-3.8.2"}, "iso_27001-2013": "A.14.2.5,A.8.1.3", "mitre_mitigations": "M1028", "pci_dss_v4": {"0": "1.1.1,1.2.1,1.2.6,1.2.7,1.3.1,1.5.1,2.1.1,2.2.1,7.1"}, "soc_2": "CC5.2,CC6.1,CC7.1,CC8.1", "pci_dss_v3": {"2": {"1": "11.5,2.2,7.1,7.1.1,7.1.2,7.1.3"}}, "cis_csc_v7": "5.1"}, "description": "Setting the sticky bit on world writable directories prevents users from deleting or renaming files in that directory that are not owned by them.", "id": "31180", "title": "Ensure sticky bit is set on all world-writable directories.", "rationale": "This feature prevents the ability to delete or rename files in world writable directories (such as /tmp ) that are owned by another user.", "command": ["sh -c \"df --local -P 2> /dev/null | awk '{if (NR!=1) print $6}' | xargs -I '{}' find '{}' -xdev -type d \\\\( -perm -0002 -a ! -perm -1000 \\\\) 2>/dev/null\""]}, "type": "check", "policy": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0."}}, "rule": {"cis_csc_v8": ["3.3", "4.1"], "mail": false, "level": 3, "pci_dss": ["2.2"], "tsc": ["CC7.1", "CC7.2"], "hipaa": ["164.308(a)(3)(i)", "164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A)", "164.312(a)(1)"], "nist_sp_800-53": ["AC-5", "AC-6", "CM-7(1)", "CM-9", "SA-10"], "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure sticky bit is set on all world-writable directories.", "groups": ["sca"], "mitre_tactics": ["TA0004"], "mitre_techniques": ["T1548"], "cis": ["6.1.13"], "iso_27001-2013": ["A.14.2.5", "A.8.1.3"], "nist_800_53": ["CM.1"], "mitre_mitigations": ["M1028"], "gdpr": ["IV_35.7.d"], "firedtimes": 175, "soc_2": ["CC5.2", "CC6.1", "CC7.1", "CC8.1"], "id": "19009", "cis_csc_v7": ["5.1"]}, "decoder": {"name": "sca"}, "input": {"type": "log"}, "@timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.882Z", "location": "sca", "id": "1776413938.1390499", "timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.882+0000"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.872+0000", "rule_id": "19008", "severity": "INFO", "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure permissions on /etc/gshadow- are configured.", "source_ip": "Unknown", "agent": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "full_alert": {"agent": {"name": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "id": "001"}, "manager": {"name": "wazuh.manager"}, "data": {"sca": {"scan_id": "319070859", "check": {"result": "passed", "remediation": "Run the following commands to set mode, owner, and group on /etc/gshadow-: # chown root:root /etc/gshadow- # chmod 0000 /etc/gshadow-.", "compliance": {"cis_csc_v8": "3.3", "hipaa": "164.308(a)(3)(i),164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A),164.312(a)(1)", "nist_sp_800-53": "AC-5,AC-6", "mitre_tactics": "TA0005", "mitre_techniques": "T1003, T1003.008, T1222, T1222.002", "cis": "6.1.9", "cmmc_v2": {"0": "AC.L1-3.1.1,AC.L1-3.1.2,AC.L2-3.1.3,AC.L2-3.1.5,MP.L2-3.8.2"}, "iso_27001-2013": "A.10.1.1", "mitre_mitigations": "M1022", "pci_dss_v4": {"0": "1.3.1,7.1"}, "soc_2": "CC5.2,CC6.1", "pci_dss_v3": {"2": {"1": "7.1,7.1.1,7.1.2,7.1.3"}}, "cis_csc_v7": "16.4"}, "description": "The /etc/gshadow- file is used to store backup information about groups that is critical to the security of those accounts, such as the hashed password and other security information.", "id": "31179", "title": "Ensure permissions on /etc/gshadow- are configured.", "rationale": "It is critical to ensure that the /etc/gshadow- file is protected from unauthorized access. Although it is protected by default, the file permissions could be changed either inadvertently or through malicious actions.", "command": ["stat -Lc \"%n %a %u %U %g %G\" /etc/gshadow-"]}, "type": "check", "policy": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0."}}, "rule": {"cis_csc_v8": ["3.3"], "mail": false, "level": 3, "pci_dss": ["2.2"], "tsc": ["CC7.1", "CC7.2"], "hipaa": ["164.308(a)(3)(i)", "164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A)", "164.312(a)(1)"], "nist_sp_800-53": ["AC-5", "AC-6"], "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure permissions on /etc/gshadow- are configured.", "groups": ["sca"], "mitre_tactics": ["TA0005"], "mitre_techniques": ["T1003", "T1003.008", "T1222", "T1222.002"], "cis": ["6.1.9"], "iso_27001-2013": ["A.10.1.1"], "nist_800_53": ["CM.1"], "mitre_mitigations": ["M1022"], "gdpr": ["IV_35.7.d"], "firedtimes": 99, "soc_2": ["CC5.2", "CC6.1"], "id": "19008", "cis_csc_v7": ["16.4"]}, "decoder": {"name": "sca"}, "input": {"type": "log"}, "@timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.872Z", "location": "sca", "id": "1776413938.1387115", "timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.872+0000"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.862+0000", "rule_id": "19008", "severity": "INFO", "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure permissions on /etc/gshadow are configured.", "source_ip": "Unknown", "agent": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "full_alert": {"agent": {"name": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "id": "001"}, "manager": {"name": "wazuh.manager"}, "data": {"sca": {"scan_id": "319070859", "check": {"result": "passed", "remediation": "Run the following commands to set mode, owner, and group on /etc/gshadow: # chown root:root /etc/gshadow # chmod 0000 /etc/gshadow.", "compliance": {"cis_csc_v8": "3.3", "hipaa": "164.308(a)(3)(i),164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A),164.312(a)(1)", "nist_sp_800-53": "AC-3,MP-2", "mitre_tactics": "TA0005", "mitre_techniques": "T1003, T1003.008, T1222, T1222.002", "cis": "6.1.8", "cmmc_v2": {"0": "AC.L1-3.1.1,AC.L1-3.1.2,AC.L2-3.1.3,AC.L2-3.1.5,MP.L2-3.8.2"}, "iso_27001-2013": "A.10.1.1", "mitre_mitigations": "M1022", "pci_dss_v4": {"0": "1.3.1,7.1"}, "soc_2": "CC5.2,CC6.1", "pci_dss_v3": {"2": {"1": "7.1,7.1.1,7.1.2,7.1.3"}}, "cis_csc_v7": "16.4"}, "description": "The /etc/gshadow file is used to store the information about groups that is critical to the security of those accounts, such as the hashed password and other security information.", "id": "31178", "title": "Ensure permissions on /etc/gshadow are configured.", "rationale": "If attackers can gain read access to the /etc/gshadow file, they can easily run a password cracking program against the hashed password to break it. Other security information that is stored in the /etc/gshadow file (such as group administrators) could also be useful to subvert the group.", "command": ["stat -Lc \"%n %a %u %U %g %G\" /etc/gshadow"]}, "type": "check", "policy": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0."}}, "rule": {"cis_csc_v8": ["3.3"], "mail": false, "level": 3, "pci_dss": ["2.2"], "tsc": ["CC7.1", "CC7.2"], "hipaa": ["164.308(a)(3)(i)", "164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A)", "164.312(a)(1)"], "nist_sp_800-53": ["AC-3", "MP-2"], "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure permissions on /etc/gshadow are configured.", "groups": ["sca"], "mitre_tactics": ["TA0005"], "mitre_techniques": ["T1003", "T1003.008", "T1222", "T1222.002"], "cis": ["6.1.8"], "iso_27001-2013": ["A.10.1.1"], "nist_800_53": ["CM.1"], "mitre_mitigations": ["M1022"], "gdpr": ["IV_35.7.d"], "firedtimes": 98, "soc_2": ["CC5.2", "CC6.1"], "id": "19008", "cis_csc_v7": ["16.4"]}, "decoder": {"name": "sca"}, "input": {"type": "log"}, "@timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.862Z", "location": "sca", "id": "1776413938.1383609", "timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.862+0000"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.851+0000", "rule_id": "19008", "severity": "INFO", "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure permissions on /etc/shadow- are configured.", "source_ip": "Unknown", "agent": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "full_alert": {"agent": {"name": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "id": "001"}, "manager": {"name": "wazuh.manager"}, "data": {"sca": {"scan_id": "319070859", "check": {"result": "passed", "remediation": "Run the following commands to set mode, owner, and group on /etc/shadow-: # chown root:root /etc/shadow- # chmod 0000 /etc/shadow-.", "compliance": {"cis_csc_v8": "3.3", "hipaa": "164.308(a)(3)(i),164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A),164.312(a)(1)", "nist_sp_800-53": "AC-3,MP-2", "mitre_tactics": "TA0005", "mitre_techniques": "T1003, T1003.008, T1222, T1222.002", "cis": "6.1.7", "cmmc_v2": {"0": "AC.L1-3.1.1,AC.L1-3.1.2,AC.L2-3.1.3,AC.L2-3.1.5,MP.L2-3.8.2"}, "iso_27001-2013": "A.10.1.1", "mitre_mitigations": "M1022", "pci_dss_v4": {"0": "1.3.1,7.1"}, "soc_2": "CC5.2,CC6.1", "pci_dss_v3": {"2": {"1": "7.1,7.1.1,7.1.2,7.1.3"}}, "cis_csc_v7": "16.4"}, "description": "The /etc/shadow- file is used to store backup information about user accounts that is critical to the security of those accounts, such as the hashed password and other security information.", "id": "31177", "title": "Ensure permissions on /etc/shadow- are configured.", "rationale": "It is critical to ensure that the /etc/shadow- file is protected from unauthorized access. Although it is protected by default, the file permissions could be changed either inadvertently or through malicious actions.", "command": ["stat -Lc \"%n %a %u %U %g %G\" /etc/shadow-"]}, "type": "check", "policy": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0."}}, "rule": {"cis_csc_v8": ["3.3"], "mail": false, "level": 3, "pci_dss": ["2.2"], "tsc": ["CC7.1", "CC7.2"], "hipaa": ["164.308(a)(3)(i)", "164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A)", "164.312(a)(1)"], "nist_sp_800-53": ["AC-3", "MP-2"], "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure permissions on /etc/shadow- are configured.", "groups": ["sca"], "mitre_tactics": ["TA0005"], "mitre_techniques": ["T1003", "T1003.008", "T1222", "T1222.002"], "cis": ["6.1.7"], "iso_27001-2013": ["A.10.1.1"], "nist_800_53": ["CM.1"], "mitre_mitigations": ["M1022"], "gdpr": ["IV_35.7.d"], "firedtimes": 97, "soc_2": ["CC5.2", "CC6.1"], "id": "19008", "cis_csc_v7": ["16.4"]}, "decoder": {"name": "sca"}, "input": {"type": "log"}, "@timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.851Z", "location": "sca", "id": "1776413938.1380229", "timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.851+0000"}}
{"timestamp": "2026-04-17T08:18:58.841+0000", "rule_id": "19008", "severity": "INFO", "description": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0.: Ensure permissions on /etc/shadow are configured.", "source_ip": "Unknown", "agent": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "full_alert": {"agent": {"name": "wazuh-agent-ad7f6ffce373", "id": "001"}, "manager": {"name": "wazuh.manager"}, "data": {"sca": {"scan_id": "319070859", "check": {"result": "passed", "remediation": "Run the following commands to set mode, owner, and group on /etc/shadow: # chown root:root /etc/shadow # chmod 0000 /etc/shadow.", "compliance": {"cis_csc_v8": "3.3", "hipaa": "164.308(a)(3)(i),164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A),164.312(a)(1)", "nist_sp_800-53": "AC-3,MP-2", "mitre_tactics": "TA0005", "mitre_techniques": "T1003, T1003.008, T1222, T1222.002", "cis": "6.1.6", "cmmc_v2": {"0": "AC.L1-3.1.1,AC.L1-3.1.2,AC.L2-3.1.3,AC.L2-3.1.5,MP.L2-3.8.2"}, "iso_27001-2013": "A.10.1.1", "mitre_mitigations": "M1022", "pci_dss_v4": {"0": "1.3.1,7.1"}, "soc_2": "CC5.2,CC6.1", "pci_dss_v3": {"2": {"1": "7.1,7.1.1,7.1.2,7.1.3"}}, "cis_csc_v7": "16.4"}, "description": "The /etc/shadow file is used to store the information about user accounts that is critical to the security of those accounts, such as the hashed password and other security information.", "id": "31176", "title": "Ensure permissions on /etc/shadow are configured.", "rationale": "If attackers can gain read access to the /etc/shadow file, they can easily run a password cracking program against the hashed password to break it. Other security information that is stored in the /etc/shadow file (such as expiration) could also be useful to subvert the user accounts.", "command": ["stat -Lc \"%n %a %u %U %g %G\" /etc/shadow"]}, "type": "check", "policy": "CIS Benchmark for Amazon Linux 2023 Benchmark v1.0.0."}}, "rule": {"cis_csc_v8": ["3.3"], "mail": false, "level": 3, "pci_dss": ["2.2"], "tsc": ["CC7.1", "CC7.2"], "hipaa": ["164.308(a)(3)(i)", "164.308(a)(3)(ii)(A)", "16